This paper focuses on the problem of video generation from unlabeled data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method uses generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with motion and appearance information in videos, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
